{
  "texts": [
    "Usually, the detection takes between 50 -200 ms depending on which modalities (face, head, body, or any combination of them) are involved and which movement thresholds are defined.",
    "After that period, a suitable action is selected, and after a defined delay is shown by the SIA.",
    "The delay is usually between 500 -2000 ms (or longer), and the observable reaction of the SIA usually takes as long as the detected social signal but can be altered concerning timing and intensity.",
    "The minimal system intrinsic reaction time is between 100 -400 ms + 20 ms (max.",
    "approximated) inter software module delay."
  ]
}